peopleAlsoAsk.question: What are the values of cameras?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: ISO values come in numbers such as 100 and 400. A higher (larger) value means that the camera is sensitive to light, letting you shoot in dark environments, capture quickly-moving subjects, and also prevent blurring caused by hand movement. However, higher values also generate more noise and reduce image quality.
